revision.text:
'''Alvin''' is a small [[Impact crater|crater]] lying situated within the [[Margaritifer Sinus quadrangle]] (MC-19) of the planet [[Mars]]. It was visited by the [[Opportunity rover]] in 2005. It is near the location called Opportunity's Site 43.<ref>Nasa Mars Exploration - Panoramas: Opportunity [http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/mer/gallery/panoramas/opportunity/2005.html 08-Mar-2005, Opportunity's View, Sol 381]</ref>

