Dr. '''John W. Kebabian''' is a neuropharmacologist and [[neuroscientist]] who was the first to discover that there were multiple subtypes of [[dopamine receptor]]s. His pioneering work which was published in 1979 revolutionized the understanding of the role of dopamine receptors in cognition, movement and mental disorders.<ref name="Daly1984">{{cite journal|last=Daly|first=Jeffrey M.|author2=Salloway, Stephen|date=1 May 1994|title=Dopamine Receptors in the Human Brain|journal=[[Psychiatric Times]]|volume=11|issue=5|url=http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/display/article/10168/49076|accessdate=18 August 2010}}</ref>

