{{Infobox journal | title = Spatial Economic Analysis | editor = Bernard Fingleton | discipline = [[Economics]] | abbreviation = Spatial Econ. Anal. | publisher = [[Routledge]] on behalf of the [[Regional Studies Association]] and the British and Irish Section of the [[Regional Science Association International]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2006-present | impact = 1.375 | impact-year = 2012 | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=aimsScope&journalCode=rsea20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rsea20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rsea20 | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1742-1772 | eISSN = 1742-1780 | OCLC = 75496516 | LCCN = | CODEN = }} '''''Spatial Economic Analysis''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the development of theory and methods in [[spatial economics]]. It is published by [[Routledge]] on behalf of the [[Regional Studies Association]] and the British and Irish Section of the [[Regional Science Association International]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Bernard Fingleton ([[University of Cambridge]]).
