'''Thanatocoensis''' (from [[Greek language]] ''thanatos'' - death and ''koinos'' - common) are all the embedded [[fossil]]s at a single discovery site. This site may be referred to as a '''death assemblage'''. Such groupings are composed of fossils of organisms which may not have been associated during life, often originating from different habitats. Examples include marine fossils having been brought together by a [[current (stream)|water current]] or animal bones having been deposited by a predator.

